While this discussion seems to be turning into a Ragefire discussion and I wish not go get away from it, I know this discussion was first started with a number of other questions at the same time.  With that in mind, I have a question or 2 about some things that were brought up in answers to a couple of Broken's questions.<br>
<br>
Broken asked about the 6 person invite rule of other guilds going on a different planar raid than their guilds.  What was answered was that each guild can reserve a plane once per month and that other guilds respect that reservation.  While I agree with this and have been on a number of raids myself, I wonder what happens on those days that no reservation has been made.<br>
<br>
Can a guild who has made a reservation for a planar raid on a specific day in a given month also go into a plane for a raid that noone has reserved for that day?  Is this considered bad form?  Example... Undertakers alliance has Hate reserved for a Saturday in a month, if we wanted to, could the Undertakers alliance also go to Hate say on a Tuesday or Thursday when Hate is not normally reserved?  I'm not saying that we would do this, it's just a question that came to my mind during all this reading I've done on this subject.<br>
<br>
One thing that Broken, or anyone else who may have questions concerning being able to take down Ragefire, General V'Ghera, or any other difficult Epic mob, if you have friends or have accuaintences (sp), chances are if you ask for help taking one of them down, you can always get help doing so on The Rathe.  At least this is how it's been in my experience.  Even if you do not belong to a guild, you may have a guild invite you on one of their raids just for you to get your Epic piece, such as what happened with me joining Legend of Marr against the General or one of my guildmates being helped by Tindi Losi in Chardok.  The possibilities are there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Having the respect from these guilds goes along way to completing a major quest if you need help doing it.<br>
